source_code.code:
public class SleepTest {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
		for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
			System.out.println(i);
			Thread.sleep(1000);
		}
	}

}

Bug.WithStack:
I don't know if this is a UI bug, or a Debug related bug.

I ran this test in Windows XP Professional, Sun JDK 1.5.0.

- Run the following program:

public class SleepTest {
	
	public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
		for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
			System.out.println(i);
			Thread.sleep(1000);
		}
	}

}

- Open the Data/Time Properties.
- Stay changing the year many times, back and foward.
- I don't know exactly what makes the bug happen, and it is a little hard to
make this happen, but sometimes the console will stop displaying the output from
the program.
- I know this is a Console View issue, because if you redirect the launch output
to a file (Launch Properties -> Common tab -> Standard Input and Output ->
File), you will see that the file stay been updated when the console stops.
Deferred
As of now 'LATER' and 'REMIND' resolutions are no longer supported.
Please reopen this bug if it is still valid for you.

