Bug.WithStack:
The search with the following pattern:
SearchEngine.createSearchPattern("::GenClass1::GenClass1(void)", ICSearchConstants.METHOD, DEFINITIONS, CASE_SENSITIVE);
Returns no matches (both .h and .cpp file with declaration and definition for the GenClass1::GenClass1() were present in the workspace).
Search is executed via SearchEngine().search(workspace, pattern, scope, collector, true, this);
The workspace contains C++ project indexed with either "Original" or "DOM/AST" indexer. I also tried to change search string to "::GenClass1::GenClass1()" which didn't produce any effect. This has been fixed for a while - can verify in RC2.
- BG

